As a final instance of value mismatch, let us consider again the somewhat puzzling situation encountered earlier: In most cases (and for most Thai speakers) the combination
path verb + deictic verb + LM-NP (49c) is ungrammatical, while path verb + deictic verb (49a) and path verb + LM-NP (49c) are unproblematic. Interposing an appropriate region
noun between the deictic verb and the LM-NP also “cancels out” the ungrammaticality (49d).

(49) a. b. c. d.

