pratuu door
LM

Finally, let us recall example (10), here repeated as (52), showing that unassisted, Thai path verbs fail to anchor the spatial utterance, i.e. to express a value for Frame of
Reference, while they do so in combination with either manner verbs, or other classes which do express FoR. Thus, we may formulate a general semantic condition on
grammaticality: At least one FoR needs to be overtly expressed in the spatial utterance.

(52) ??kha&w

(kamlaN) kha^w/?ç$çk/l´´y/kla$p/pha$an/kha^am

