5 In the Thai “forg story” corpus (Zlatev and Yangklang 2003b), constisting of 50 narratives and 23554 word tokens kha^aN occurs 40 times, thaaN 10 times (including lexical noun and preposition uses), da^an 2 times, bµ^aN 2 times and phaay only once. 6 The polysemy nµ&µa (‘North’, ‘above’) and ta^ay (‘South’, ‘below’) is probably due to the geography of Thailand, which is more mountainous in the North and more flat in the South, rather than the conventional directionality of maps, even though it seems to be synchronically reinforced by the current use of such maps in Thailand.
